{
  "text": "A discriminated avoidance task described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ) was used to assess learning for simple avoidance and simple discrimination, discrimination reversal, learning of a response strategy, and delayed memory performance. The apparatus consisted of an acrylic T-shaped maze with compartments in the stem and each goal arm separated by doors. The maze rested on a grid floor wired to deliver 0.27 mA scrambled shock to the feet.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22202269",
    "[CITATION_2]": "25564786"
